gomodel:SYNGO_460  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Serial section analysis of electron microscopic (EM) images in the hippocampus, neocortex, striatum, and amygdala showed that Cav2.3 is preferentially localized postsynaptically in dendritic shafts and spines and, to a lesser extent, in presynaptic compartments. Particles were seen to be diffusely distributed along the plasma membrane of dendrites and the spines without any preference for specialized membrane compartments.\n\nQuantitative counting of membrane bound immunoparticles in sections taken from the proximal part of the stratum radiatum (PSR) of CA1 found that 78.2% of particles were in postsynaptic compartments (dendritic shafts and spines) compared to 21.8% in presynaptic compartments. Postsynaptically, 47.7% of the observed particles were in dendritic shafts and 30.5% in the spines\n\nCav2.3 knock-out (KO) mice were used to validate the specificity of immunolabeling.. Experimental description: In this study, 2-3-month-old adult male C57BL/6 mice (n = 10), and age-matched, sex-matched Cav2.3 knock-out (KO) mice (n = 7) and postnatal day 20 rats (n = 2) were used.\n\n25/4/2017 Pim\n- rats only used in Fig.6 not used for this annotation." , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099055 replaced by GO:0045211" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-4022-8707" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2533-9548" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1212-5623" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7480-0826" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-5648-066X" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_460" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

